title: Beau Medcraft speaks about surviving jumping castle tragedy at Hillcrest Primary School Tasmania
description: Beau Medcraft, now 14, suffered two broken arms and a shattered wrist after he fell 10 metres from a bouncing castle that got caught up in a 'mini-tornado' at Hillcrest Primary School.

title: Puppies and pregnant dogs abandoned by 'money-maker' breeders leaving rescue centres overwhelmed
description: These three little puppies should have been destined for loving homes - but then the market for them collapsed.

title: Reserve Bank board member Ian Harper makes a shocking admission  about interest rates
description: A Reserve Bank of Australia executive has made a shocking admission, saying the organisation's so far failed efforts to curb inflation have been 'a terrible job'.

title: ANDREW PIERCE asks: Will 'puerile' posturing cost the BMA vital public support?
description: ANDREW PIERCE: Dr Robert Laurenson, 28, (pictured) co-chairman of the BMA junior doctors' committee, barely uttered a word during the 30-minute meeting with Steve Barclay.

title: China wants Labour government as it is soft on security, leaked US intelligence documents claim
description: According to American analysis, China thinks it could achieve more 'success', due to Starmer's reluctance to send a Royal Navy aircraft carrier to the region.

title: Embarrassed by his British roots: President Joe Biden has shown disdain for his UK heritage
description: Despite proudly speaking about his 'Irishness', Mr Biden has caused controversy with his jokes and jibes about the British - even hinting at his 'embarrassment' over his father's UK ancestors.

title: New York City gets an early taste of summer as 'Bermuda high' sends temperatures soaring to 83F
description: New York City is getting a taste of summer in early April, as temperatures broke 80 degrees Wednesday for the first time this year, with the heat expected to stay through the end of week.
